			<p>So, what can we do, whether in lockdown or not? </p>
			
			<p>One of the important aspects to understand is that being in lockdown is not normal for our well-being. So what can we do? </p>
			 
			 <P>Here are some action steps I recommend:

				1.       Stay active weather you are at home or out. 
				
				2.      Walk, take stairs, play ball with kids.
				
				3.     If you can’t walk outside, consider yoga, or indoor games.
				
				4.     Set some daily goals, schedule in some activity together.</P>
			 
			 <P> Set Smart Goals with an example: 

				1.       Specific- adding daily activities such as go outside with kids 
				
				2.      Measurable - 10 to 15 minutes daily 
				
				3.     Attainable - part of a healthy lifestyle 
				
				4.     Relevant - important to prevent illness 
				
				5.     Time based- set a goal weekly and add 10 minutes more each week. </P>
		
